The paper proposes a machine comprehension model that uses deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The model also involves encoding and matching techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of bi-directional LSTMs, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
